To prevent this you could use CONST instead of VAR

What is the difference between var and let?

Let is used to declare variables that only exist within a code block. Let can be reassignmed but not redeclared (Unlike var ). 
What is the difference between var and const?

Var can be reassigned and const cannot. Var can be redeclared and const cannot.

What is the difference between let and const?
main difference is that let can be reassigned and const cannot.

What is hoisting?
It's when the execution appears to move the declaration of functions to the top of the scope.

